 The Lagos State Police Command has reportedly foiled an attempt by some men of the underworld to attack Dangote Refinery within the Lekki Free Trade Zone in Lagos State. Benjamin Hundeyin (SP), the Police Public Relations Officer, Lagos State Command, made the disclosure in a statement on Tuesday. The statement quoted the PPRO as saying that the attack occurred in the early hours of Monday. It read that the armed gang were repelled while attempting to cart away some installed armored cables in the refinery. The statement read that “The hoodlums, (numbering) about 20, who gained access to the refinery through the lagoon side, were repelled. “On sighting security operatives, they fled the scene.” The statement indicated that one of the hoodlums lost his life in a crossfire. It read, “One of the hoodlums was hit in the ensuing gunfire and died on the way to the hospital. “Investigation has commenced with a view to arresting the fleeing attackers. “On the directive of the Commissioner of Police, Lagos State Command, Abiodun Alabi, security at the refinery has been fortified.” 